main event: Two hovering lights were observed in the sky east of the Maple Valley Highway near Renton, Washington on March 26, 1957.
interesting points: The lights appeared to move around in a jagged flight path and changed direction and speed rapidly, indicating they were intelligently controlled and possibly some type of aircraft.
The lights were observed for approximately 2 minutes.
The sighting was also reported to the Washington State Patrol, who investigated but could not find the source of the lights by 1935Z.
The report suggests the lights may have been from an airway beacon located 3 miles east of the sighting location.
The report includes detailed coordinates and descriptions of the location and movement of the lights.
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including a neighbor and the Washington State Patrol
photographs: no photographs included in the report
